race.comment: LA ROSETTA (7) has ability but turned in an out of character run fresh when dropped right out. Fitter and worth noting won only try course and distance and only other try second-up. Low drawn and can atone. PERFUME RIVER (10) was solid fresh over 1450m when settled off speed, moved up to share lead turning then was swamped late. Fitter again and worth noting sole career win did come when second-up from a break. Extra trip a plus and looks a leading player.  SHEER LUNACY (5) is a seasoned galloper who has been well held at the last few of outings, the latest when sixth and beaten 4 lengths over 1450m at Kilmore. Worth noting though all three have been on top of the ground and he is far better in these conditions. Rates highly and can return to form.  GOLD TRACKER (9) wasn't far away last time and gets chance to improve.
